SIMPLE: sailor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sailor
<hw>Sail"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who follows the
business of navigating ships or other vessels; one who understands the
practical management of ships; one of the crew of a vessel; a mariner; a
common seaman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Mariner; seaman; seafarer.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sailor's choice</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <cd>An excellent marine food fish (<spn>Diplodus
rhomboides</spn>, syn. <spn>Lagodon rhomboides</spn>) of the
<geog>Southern United States</geog>; -- called also
<altname>porgy</altname>, <altname>squirrel fish</altname>,
<altname>yellowtail</altname>, and <altname>salt-water
bream</altname>.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>A species of grunt
(<spn>Orthopristis chrysopterus</spn> syn. <spn>Pomadasys
chrysopterus</spn>), an excellent food fish common on the southern
coasts of the United States; -- called also <altname>hogfish</altname>,
and <altname>pigfish</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saily</ent>⟦br⟧
